The People’s Democratic Party (PDP) candidate for Nangere/Potiskum Federal Constituency in the 2023 general elections, Adamu Abubakar Waziri has vowed to offer good representation and good legislation if given the mandate in the forthcoming elections. Waziri made the plea on Wednesday during an interview with a Daily Independent correspondent in Damaturu. According to him voting for PDP in Nangere, Potiskum federal constituency “will certainly bring tremendous change and development to the people, we will empower the teeming unemployed youths, attract support to the farmers, secure infrastructural development among others. “ “Our people require full and proper representation at the federal legislature for rapid growth in education, health, infrastructure, road construction, housing and many more, we promise to sponsor bills that will be for the growth and development of the youth, women and the elderly,” he said.